  "prompt": "What is the weather in orlando like in January?",
  "response": "In January, the weather in Orlando, Florida is generally mild and pleasant. Average high temperatures typically range from the upper 60s to low 70s Fahrenheit (around 20-23 degrees Celsius), while average low temperatures are in the upper 40s to low 50s Fahrenheit (around 8-12 degrees Celsius). January is one of the cooler months of the year in Orlando, but it is still relatively warm compared to many other parts of the United States. Rainfall is usually moderate, with occasional showers. Overall, it\u2019s a comfortable time to visit with a mix of sunny and cloudy days.",
